---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterForm from '../components/NewsletterForm.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Nathaniel Senyo Gemegah"
  description="Placeholder about page for Nathaniel Senyo Gemegah – story, background, and what he is working on."
>
  <article class="space-y-12">
    <header class="space-y-4">
      <h1 class="page-heading">
        About Nathaniel Senyo Gemegah
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base md:text-lg text-black/80 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        This page is placeholder space for Pete&apos;s story: who he is, what he cares about, and how he arrived at the work he&apos;s doing today. Replace all of this text with your own voice and details.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Who I Am
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        Use this section to introduce yourself in a grounded, human way. For now, this paragraph is only placeholder text describing your background, interests, and the kind of work that energizes you.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        What I&apos;ve Done
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        Summarize key milestones or highlights from your journey so far. This could include projects, businesses, collaborations, or experiments. Replace this placeholder copy with concise, specific examples.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        What I&apos;m Focused on Now
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        Share what currently has your attention. This placeholder text stands in for a short explanation of what you&apos;re building, learning, or exploring at the moment, and why it matters to you.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        How This Newsletter Fits In
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        Explain how your newsletter ties all of this together&mdash;what readers can expect and why it&apos;s worth their attention. Replace this with a simple, direct pitch written in your own words.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-4 border-t border-black/10">
      <NewsletterForm compact={true} />
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

